name: Doris
description: Digital collage (2400x3200px) Doris (minor planet designation: 48 Doris) is one of the largest main belt asteroids. To find a name for the object, Jacques Babinet of the Academy of Sciences created a shortlist and asked the geologist Élie de Beaumont to make the selection. De Beaumont chose Doris, after an Oceanid in Greek mythology. Since Doris was discovered on the same night as 49 Pales, de Deaumont suggested naming the two "The Twins"
